 ('6', '5', '4', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Explore\",\"slug\":\"explore\",\"postDate\":1519852580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"4\":\"<ul><li>First ascent of the Shark\\u2019s Fin on Meru<\\/li><li>Mallory and Irvine Research Expedition, Everest<\\/li><li>First ascent of Rakekniven Peak, Queen Maud Land, Antarctica<\\/li><li>First ascent of the East Face of Vinson Massif, Ellsworth Mountains, Antarctica<\\/li><li>Stump\\/Anker Route, Streaked Wall, VI 5.11 A4 4\\/90 fa Zion, Utah<\\/li><li>Winner of the 2015 Sundance US Documentary Audience Award<\\/li><li>Honorary PHD from University of Utah<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"3\":\"<p>Conrad Anker is a climber\\u2019s climber, at home on a faraway alpine wall or the sparkling ice of his home canyon, Hyalite, located in the Gallatin Range of southwestern Montana. Over decades in the mountains, he has come to value the rarified air of Antarctica, the Himalaya and Montana equally; inspired by the value of immersion in other ecosystems and cultures, he\\u2019s become more fully enmeshed in both the physical and communal landscape of his hometown of Bozeman. Conrad came to climbing by way of his family, learning a deep appreciation for the outdoors from his California childhood, an appreciation and respect that has deepened as climbing took him around the world.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Conrad is still climbing at full throttle. The master of technical mountaineering and Captain of The North Face Global Athlete Team has over 30 years of experience under his belt, yet is still chasing first ascents. In 2011, he summited the Shark\\u2019s Fin, one of the last unclimbed Himalayan peaks, and in 2012, led an expedition to recreate the historic 1963 American Mount Everest Expedition. He\\u2019s a visionary, a champion for the environment, a pioneer and the best comrade you\\u2019ll find at 25,000 feet&mdash;he\\u2019s dedicated every ounce of his being to this life. Legendary doesn\\u2019t even begin to describe him.<\\/p>\",\"14\":\"\",\"21\":\"\",\"5\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"rightSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"Expedition Antarctica\",\"videoLink\":\"Coming Soon\",\"expeditionDescription\":\"Facing extreme and challenging conditions, the goal of this month-long expedition is to reach as many summits of the Wolf\\u2019s Jaw massif as possible.\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"8\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.nationalgeographic.com\\/adventure\\/destinations\\/antarctica\\/expedition-antarctica\\/\",\"purchaseLink\":\"\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"leftSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"Meru\",\"videoLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=YvS6O9lVkkg \",\"expeditionBody\":\"After suffering dramatic setbacks in their lives, three close friends who are among the world\\u2019s best professional climbers battle their complicated pasts, inner demons and nature\\u2019s harshest elements in an attempt to confront the Shark\\u2019s Fin on Mount Meru, the most technically complicated and dangerous peak in the Himalayas, one that has never been scaled to completion.\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"10\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"http:\\/\\/www.merufilm.com\\/\",\"purchaseLink\":\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/movie\\/meru\\/id1030748788?mt=6&ign-itsct=1030748788-1030748788&ign-itscg=0177&ign-mpt=uo%3D4\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"rightSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"Always Above Us\",\"videoLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=xOm6Nktxof4 \",\"expeditionDescription\":\"Leading the life of a climber involves a tremendous amount of sacrifice and hardship, but for team athletes Conrad Anker and Kris Erickson, there\'s no living without it. \",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"11\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.thenorthface.com\\/about-us\\/expeditions\\/always-above-us-2014.html\",\"purchaseLink\":\"\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"leftSideThumbnail\",\