ays Above Us\",\"videoLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=xOm6Nktxof4 \",\"expeditionDescription\":\"Leading the life of a climber involves a tremendous amount of sacrifice and hardship, but for team athletes Conrad Anker and Kris Erickson, there\'s no living without it. \",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"11\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.thenorthface.com\\/about-us\\/expeditions\\/always-above-us-2014.html\",\"purchaseLink\":\"\"}},\"16\":{\"type\":\"leftSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"National Parks Adventure\",\"videoLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=0iqF2Tk_1WA\",\"expeditionBody\":\"Narrated by Academy Award winner Robert Redford, National Parks Adventure takes audiences on the ultimate off-trail adventure into the nation\\u2019s awe-inspiring great outdoors and untamed wilderness.\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"12\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/nationalparksadventure.com\\/\",\"purchaseLink\":\"\"}}},\"20\":\"\"}}', '2018-03-01 01:40:33', '2018-03-01 01:40:33', '2ceb11fe-03da-40ad-b8d9-9733205e2d0e'),
 ('8', '5', '4', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Explore\",\"slug\":\"explore\",\"postDate\":1519852580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"4\":\"<ul><li>First ascent of the Shark\\u2019s Fin on Meru<\\/li><li>Mallory and Irvine Research Expedition, Everest<\\/li><li>First ascent of Rakekniven Peak, Queen Maud Land, Antarctica<\\/li><li>First ascent of the East Face of Vinson Massif, Ellsworth Mountains, Antarctica<\\/li><li>Stump\\/Anker Route, Streaked Wall, VI 5.11 A4 4\\/90 fa Zion, Utah<\\/li><li>Winner of the 2015 Sundance US Documentary Audience Award<\\/li><li>Honorary PHD from University of Utah<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"3\":\"<p>Conrad Anker is a climber\\u2019s climber, at home on a faraway alpine wall or the sparkling ice of his home canyon, Hyalite, located in the Gallatin Range of southwestern Montana. Over decades in the mountains, he has come to value the rarified air of Antarctica, the Himalaya and Montana equally; inspired by the value of immersion in other ecosystems and cultures, he\\u2019s become more fully enmeshed in both the physical and communal landscape of his hometown of Bozeman. Conrad came to climbing by way of his family, learning a deep appreciation for the outdoors from his California childhood, an appreciation and respect that has deepened as climbing took him around the world.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Conrad is still climbing at full throttle. The master of technical mountaineering and Captain of The North Face Global Athlete Team has over 30 years of experience under his belt, yet is still chasing first ascents. In 2011, he summited the Shark\\u2019s Fin, one of the last unclimbed Himalayan peaks, and in 2012, led an expedition to recreate the historic 1963 American Mount Everest Expedition. He\\u2019s a visionary, a champion for the environment, a pioneer and the best comrade you\\u2019ll find at 25,000 feet&mdash;he\\u2019s dedicated every ounce of his being to this life. Legendary doesn\\u2019t even begin to describe him.<\\/p>\",\"14\":{\"18\":{\"type\":\"timelineEvent\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfEvent\":\"Everest Expedition 2012\",\"eventBackgroundImage\":[\"17\"],\"eventDescription\":\"To climb the West Ridge and the Southeast Ridge of Mount Everest in an expedition supported by National Geographic, The North Face, and Montana State University. Team members will measure the summit, conduct groundbreaking geological research and work with The Mayo Clinic to conduct tests on high-altitude human physiology.\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"timelineEvent\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfEvent\":\"Shark\'s Fin, Meru 2011\",\"eventBackgroundImage\":[\"19\"],\"eventDescription\":\"Second attempt on the 21,000-foot mountain to get the first ascent of The Shark\'s Fin.\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"timelineEvent\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfEvent\":\"Everest Extreme Ice Survey\",\"eventBackgroundImage\":[\"20\"],\"eventDescription\":\"Boulder-based Extreme Ice Survey\\u2019s research of the world\\u2019s glaciers reached new heights this year when a field team mounted five time-lapse cameras in three locations high in the Himalayas. The cameras, mounted in late April and early May, are in position to document the changing glacial landscape on Mount Everest and the nearby mountain of Ama Dablam, focusing on the Khumbu and Nare Glaciers. Their locations were decided by Extreme Ice Survey director James Balog and well-known mountaineer Conrad Anker to match historical photographs the two found during research at the American Alpine Club Library in Golden.\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"timelineEvent\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfEvent\":\"Shark\'s Fin, Meru 2009\",\"eventBackgroundImage\":[\"21\"],\"eventDescription\":\"Jimmy Chin, Renan Ozturk, and Conrad Anker journey to the headwaters of the Ganges, on their attempt to scale the unclimbed central pillar of Mount Meru (6310 meters). Their objective was to climb the 1300 meter high altitude wall of the Shark\\u2019s Fin in big wall capsule style.\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"timelineEvent\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfEvent\":\"Everest Tibet Side 2007\",\"eventBackgroundImage\":[\"22\"],\"eventDescription\":\"The 2007 expedition team with film crew investigated Mallory and Irvine\\u2019s last journey in forensic detail and tested the durability of their clothing and equipment in the unforgiving conditions of Everest \\u2013 all to reconstruct Mallory and Irvine\\u2019s final, fateful hours. Key to the understanding of their summit attempt was to be the climbers\\u2019 attempt to climb the Second Step \\u2013 without the ladder installed by the Chinese \\u2013 a 90-foot cliff that defied every climber after Mallory for half a century. 28,140 feet high, it is the one barrier that may have stopped Mallory and Irvine from reaching the summit in 1924.\"}}},\"21\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"pressPiece\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"publication\":\"CBS This Morning\",\"articleTitle\":\"Antarctica Climbers\",\"description\":\"Hidden deep within Antarctica\'s icy terrain lie half-a-dozen mountains that few climbers have summited. One group decided to scale all six, something no one had ever done before. They completed the expedition in less than 10 days. Conrad Anker, Cedar Wright and Alex Honnold, three of the all-star North Face climbers who recently returned from that journey, join \\\"CBS This Morning\\\" to discuss their experiences.\",\"seeMoreLink\":\"http:\\/\\/www.cbs.com\\/shows\\/cbs_this_morning\\/video\\/z7irE2yRGTgDilzZYhB0qCGeddHSmVEe\\/climbers-on-scaling-antarctica-mountains-spirit-of-exploration\\/\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"pressPiece\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"publication\":\"National Geographic\",\"articleTitle\":\"Expedition Antarctica\",\"description\":\"A team of six accomplished American climbers are currently exploring Queen Maud Land, an otherworldly territory of Antarctica. Facing extreme and challenging conditions, the goal of this month-long expedition is to reach as many summits of the Wolf\\u2019s Jaw massif as possible.\",\"seeMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.nationalgeographic.com\\/adventure\\/destinations\\/antarctica\\/expedition-antarctica\\/ \"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"pressPiece\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"publication\":\"Men\'s Journal\",\"articleTitle\":\"Life Advice from Conrad Anker\",\"description\":\"A collection of life\'s pressing questions, answered candidly by Conrad Anker.\",\"seeMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.mensjournal.com\\/adventure\\/life-advice-from-conrad-anker-w201283\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"pressPiece\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"publication\":\"Outside Magazine\",\"articleTitle\":\"An Icy Michigan Landscape Becomes Conrad Anker\\u2019s Playground\",\"description\":\"A collection of images and captured during the filming of National Parks Adventure.\",\"seeMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.outsideonline.com\\/2066486\\/icy-michigan-landscape-becomes-conrad-ankers-playground \"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"pressPiece\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"publication\":\"Gear Junkie\",\"articleTitle\":\"Hyalite Alpine: Climbing Ice With Conrad Anker\",\"description\":\"We\\u2019re in Hyalite Canyon, an alpine wonderland above Anker\\u2019s hometown of Bozeman, Mont., looking up at a dark corner of dripping stone and ice. \",\"seeMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/gearjunkie.com\\/featured\\/ice-climbing-conrad-anker-hyalite\"}},\"new6\":{\"type\":\"pressPiece\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"publication\":\"Outside Magazine\",\"articleTitle\":\"How Conrad Risked it All to Chase a Dream\",\"description\":\"After winning the coveted audience award at Sundance, the documentary \'Meru\' is getting a nationwide theatrical release next month. How did a climbing movie break through with mainstream audiences? Credit the incredible story at its center: a tale of tragedy, family, friendship, risk, and the redemptive power of suffering.\",\"seeMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.outsideonline.com\\/1990471\\/meru-conrad-anker-profile\"}}},\"5\":{\"13\":{\"type\":\"rightSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"Expedition Antarctica\",\"videoLink\":\"Coming Soon\",\"expeditionDescription\":\"Facing extreme and challenging conditions, the goal of this month-long expedition is to reach as many summits of the Wolf\\u2019s Jaw massif as possible.\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"8\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.nationalgeographic.com\\/adventure\\/destinations\\/antarctica\\/expedition-antarctica\\/\",\"purchaseLink\":\"\"}},\"14\":{\"type\":\"leftSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"Meru\",\"videoLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=YvS6O9lVkkg \",\"expeditionBody\":\"After suffering dramatic setbacks in their lives, three close friends who are among the world\\u2019s best professional climbers battle their complicated pasts, inner demons and nature\\u2019s harshest elements in an attempt to confront the Shark\\u2019s Fin on Mount Meru, the most technically complicated and dangerous peak in the Himalayas, one that has never been scaled to completion.\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"10\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"http:\\/\\/www.merufilm.com\\/\",\"purchaseLink\":\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/movie\\/meru\\/id1030748788?mt=6&ign-itsct=1030748788-1030748788&ign-itscg=0177&ign-mpt=uo%3D4\"}},\"15\":{\"type\":\"rightSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"Always Above Us\",\"videoLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=xOm6Nktxof4 \",\"expeditionDescription\":\"Leading the life of a climber involves a tremendous amount of sacrifice and hardship, but for team athletes Conrad Anker and Kris Erickson, there\'s no living without it. \",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"11\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.thenorthface.com\\/about-us\\/expeditions\\/always-above-us-2014.html\",\"purchaseLink\":\"\"}},\"16\":{\"type\":\"leftSideThumbnail\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfExpedition\":\"National Parks Adventure\",\"videoLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=0iqF2Tk_1WA\",\"expeditionBody\":\"Narrated by Academy Award winner Robert Redford, National Parks Adventure takes audiences on the ultimate off-trail adventure into the nation\\u2019s awe-inspiring great outdoors and untamed wilderness.\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"12\"],\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/nationalparksadventure.com\\/\",\"purchaseLink\":\"\"}}},\"20\":\"Conrad\\u2019s gear room is one of the most coveted in the world of mountaineering enthusiasts. This room is where every great expedition truly begins.\"}}', '2018-03-01 01:51:04', '2018-03-01 01:51:04', 'fc455abf-04ec-4088-8ca6-2d7bb07ab224'),
 ('9', '4', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Engage\",\"slug\":\"engage\",\"postDate\":1519852476,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"27\":\"<p>Conrad is a direct advocate for these incredible organizations<\\/p>\",\"28\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"rightSideImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfOrganization\":\"Protect Our Winters\",\"shortDescription\":\"Protect Our Winters is a passionate crew of diehards, professional athletes and industry brands mobilizing the outdoor sports community to lead the charge towards positive climate action.\",\"learnMoreLink\":\"https:\\/\\/protectourwinters.org\\/\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"33\"]}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"leftSideImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfOrganization\":\"Alex Lowe Charitable Foundation\",\"shortDescription\":\"The Alex Lowe Charitable Foundation (ALCF) is dedicated to preserving Alex Lowe\'s legacy by providing direction and financial support to sustainable, community-based humanitarian programs designed to help the people who live in remote regions of the world. This foundation carries on Alex\'s spirit of adventure.\",\"learnMoreLink\":\"http:\\/\\/www.alexlowe.org\\/\",\"thumbnailImage\":[\"34\"]}}},\"26\":\"<p>We do not just measure greatness by the peaks that we climb, or the heights that we reach, but rather by the positive impact that we create for ourselves, our communities, and our planet. Our goodness to each other is what makes us whole, and what endures for generations beyond our physical feats & achievements.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Conrad invites everyone who is inspired by the wisdom of the great outdoors to <b>engage<\\/b> in the conversation of conservation, and become an advocate for nature, and protecting our sacred mother earth.<\\/p>\",\"43\":\"<p>\\u201cEnlightenment isn\\u2019t found with a full stomach, or on a soft pillow.\\u201d&nbsp;<\\/p><p>- Conrad Anker<\\/p>\",\"48\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"date\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"dateOfEvent\":{\"date\":\"4\\/1\\/2018\"},\"titleOfEvent\":\"Website Launch\",\"locationOfEvent\":\"Bozeman, MT\",\"typeOfEvent\":\"speaking\",\"latLong\":\"45N\\/111W\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"date\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"dateOfEvent\":{\"date\":\"4\\/30\\/2018\"},\"titleOfEvent\":\"Ascend Hyalite\",\"locationOfEvent\":\"Bozeman, MT\",\"typeOfEvent\":\"adventure\",\"latLong\":\"45N\\/111W\"}}},\"37\":\"<p>Speaking to crowds in size ranging from college lecture halls to massive graduation ceremonies, Conrad reflects on lessons learned from his prodigious accomplishments, close calls, and overwhelming obstacles. Though the life of a climber seems to sometimes be fraught with innumerable challenges, Conrad\\u2019s optimism and positivity has given him the strength to endure what many would classify as impossible. And that\\u2019s a sentiment he aims to share through his words.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>I\\u2019ve learned that these things&mdash;my family, my passion for climbing and for being a force for good in the local community and in the larger community&mdash;are the source of happiness for me,\\u201d he says. \\u201cI know that life will keep changing and keep throwing new challenges my way, but my intent is always to embrace them and explore them and find a way to turn them into an experience that\\u2019s rewarding. Even when we\\u2019re suffering, whether it\\u2019s in the mountains or because of something going on at home, trying situations are a way to understand our human condition. You have to try to rise above the adversity. I like doing that.\\u201d<\\/p>\\r\\n\",\"38\":\"\",\"54\":\"Every mountaineer needs an exemplary team of partners to reach the summit. \",\"55\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"teamMember\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfMember\":\"Conrad Anker\",\"position\":\"Team Leader\",\"headshot\":[\"35\"]}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"teamMember\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfMember\":\"Pamela Hainsworth\",\"position\":\"Girl Friday\",\"headshot\":[\"36\"]}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"teamMember\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfMember\":\"Ben Ende\",\"position\":\"RXR Sports\",\"headshot\":[\"37\"]}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"teamMember\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfMember\":\"Jonathan Retseck\",\"position\":\"RXR Sports\",\"headshot\":[\"39\"]}}},\"44\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"testimonial\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfPerson\":\"Testimonial 1\",\"affiliation\":\"Company 1\",\"quote\":\"\\u201cConrad was amazing\\u201d\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"testimonial\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfPerson\":\"Testimonial 2\",\"affiliation\":\"Company 2\",\"quote\":\"\\u201cConrad was great\\u201d\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"testimonial\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"nameOfPerson\":\"Testimonial 3\",\"affiliation\":\"Company 3\",\"quote\":\"\\u201cConrad inspired us\\u201d\"}}}}}', '2018-03-01 02:04:08', '2018-03-01 02:04:08', 'c3dea8dd-806f-4ce5-99a3-ed35928e3d97'),
